data.name: MetalogixSharePointUIWinFormsMigrationTCListContentOptions_cbUseAzureUpload
data.value:
This option should only be used if you are 100% certain that your SharePoint Online tenant has the Migration Pipeline enabled.
What does this do? This migrates items and folders within the document library using a combination of Azure storage/SPO Container and the Microsoft SharePoint Online Migration Pipeline. It provides faster upload of documents into a library.
This option requires free storage space on the local hard drive that is at least 4x the largest file size in the document library that is going to be migrated using this approach.
To migrate using Azure storage, please ensure that azure storage is configured and the appropriate configuration parameters are set within Content Matrix.
To migrate using SPO Container, "Use Azure/SPO Container Office 365 Upload" and "Encrypt Azure/SPO Container Jobs" options should be checked and connection string should be blank in the EnvironmentSettings.xml or Configuration Database.
If you are unsure in the slightest then please do not use this option.

data.name: MetalogixSharePointUIWinFormsMigrationTCFolderContentOptions_cbUseAzureUpload
data.value:
This option should only be used if you are 100% certain that your SharePoint Online tenant has the Migration Pipeline enabled.
What does this do? This migrates items and folders within the document library using a combination of Azure storage/SPO Container and the Microsoft SharePoint Online Migration Pipeline. It provides faster upload of documents into a library.
This option requires free storage space on the local hard drive that is at least 4x the largest file size in the document library that is going to be migrated using this approach.
To migrate using Azure storage, please ensure that azure storage is configured and the appropriate configuration parameters are set within Content Matrix.
To migrate using SPO Container, “Use Azure/SPO Container Office 365 Upload” and “Encrypt Azure/SPO Container Jobs” options should be checked and connection string should be blank in the EnvironmentSettings.xml or Configuration Database.
If you are unsure in the slightest then please do not use this option.
